{{Infobox person |name = Adeline Ooi |image = |caption = |birth_date = 1976 |birth_place = [[Ipoh, Malaysia]] |religion = |alma_mater = [[Central Saint Martins]] |occupation = Director Asia Art Basel }}
'''Adeline Ooi''' (born 1976, Ipoh, Malaysia)is a curator and art advisor. Since January 2015, Ooi is the Director Asia for [[Art Basel]]’s show in Hong Kong.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Greenberger|first1=Alex|title=Adeline Ooi Tapped As Director Asia For Art Basel|url=http://www.artnews.com/2014/12/30/adeline-ooi-tapped-as-director-asia-for-art-basel/|agency=ArtNews|date=December 30, 2014}}</ref> She's also a member of Art Basel's Executive Committee. <ref>{{cite news|title=Why Malaysian Adeline Ooi is the perfect pick for Art Basel's Asia director|url=http://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/arts-culture/article/1677922/why-malaysian-adeline-ooi-perfect-pick-art-basels-asia|publisher=South China Morning Post|date=January 10, 2015}}</ref>
==Career and background== Ooi holds a BA (Hons) in Fine Arts from [[Central Saint Martins]], London. Ooi is the recipient of The [[Nippon Foundation]]’s Asian Public Intellectual (Junior) Fellowships Grant 2002/2003. Throughout 2003 Ooi worked on a number of regional projects in various capacities with institutions and galleries in Southeast Asia focusing mainly on Malaysian, Indonesian and Filipino contemporary art.<ref>{{cite news|last1=d'Arenberg|first1=Diana|title=A conversation with Adeline Ooi|url=https://ocula.com/magazine/conversations/adeline-ooi/|publisher=Ocala|date=March 17, 2016}}</ref> She directed and co-founded [[RogueArt]] in 2009, a cultural agency based in Malaysia, where her clients included artists, galleries, institutions, and both corporate and private collections. Between 2006 and 2008, she worked as Curator and Program Director of [[Valentine Willie Fine Art]] gallery, Kuala Lumpur.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wang|first1=Nadja|title=Interview with Adeline Ooi|url=http://www.luxuo.com/art/interview-with-adeline-ooi.html|publisher=Luxo|date=October 23, 2015}}</ref> Before becoming Director Asia for Art Basel, Ooi worked as Art Basel's VIP Relations Manager for Southeast Asia, covering Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam for two years.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Forbes|first1=Alexander|title=Art Basel Taps Art Adviser Adeline Ooi for Asia Director Post|url=https://news.artnet.com/people/art-basel-taps-art-adviser-adeline-ooi-for-asia-director-post-209877|publisher=Artnet News|date=December 30, 2014}}</ref>
