'''NUGS''',officially The '''National Union of Ghana Students''' is the largest [[student organization]] in [[Ghana]]. https://nugsonline.org.gh/about-us/ However the date of it foundation has been the subject of controversy. The official Facebook page suggests 1964,<ref>{{cite web|title=About NUGS|url=https://www.facebook.com/pages/NUGS-The-National-Union-of-Ghana-Students/189095617827852?id=189095617827852&sk=info|website=NUGS Facebook page|publisher=NUGS|accessdate=21 July 2014}}</ref> However Professor [[Anselmus Kludze]], father of [[Ave Kludze]], claimed that he was the National President of NUGS for the period 1962-1963. He says he was preceded by P.D. Vanderpuije of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology|University of Science and Technology]] (UST) and followed by Mr. F.Y.I. Fiagbe, also of the UST. He further claims that both he and Fiagbe, along with Antwi (the General Secretary at the time), Mr. Easmon and Mr. Kodwo Carr were all arrested and imprisoned without trial under the [[Preventive Detention Act]].<ref name="Sarfo">{{cite web|last1=Sarfo|first1=Samuel Adjei|title=Prof. Justice Kludze’s Take on Nkrumah’s Dictatorship. Part Five|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/Prof-Justice-Kludze-s-Take-on-Nkrumah-s-Dictatorship-Part-Five-355476|website=Ghana Web|publisher=Ghana Web|accessdate=19 January 2017}}</ref>

The organisation can trace its origins to the [[Union of Gold Coast Students in West Africa]] which was founded in the 1930s.<ref name="IRB">{{cite web|title=Information on the history of the National Union of Ghana Students (NUGS) from its founding to the present, on the executives of the NUGS in each Ghanaian university or college and on any arrests of NUGS personnel from the inception of NUGS [GHA13020], 08 February 1993|url=http://www.ecoi.net/local_link/177405/279626_en.html|publisher=IRB - Immigration and Refugee Board of Canada|accessdate=21 July 2014}}</ref> Originally the Union had as one of its aims an end to [[British colonialism|British colonial rule]] and the achievement independence.<ref name="IRB"/>

