'''Nikita Aleksandrovich Dolgushin''' ({{lang-ru|Ники́та Алекса́ндрович Долгу́шин}}; November 8, 1938, Leningrad — June 10, 2012, St. Petersburg<ref>[http://www.mikhailovsky.ru/events/umer-nikita-aleksandrovich-dolgushin Умер Никита Александрович Долгушин]</ref>) was a Russian Soviet ballet dancer, choreographer, teacher.<ref>[http://www.ballet-enc.ru/html/d/dolguqin.html Dolgushin in Encyclopedia of Ballet]</ref> She was named [[People's Artist of the USSR]] in 1988.<ref>[https://www.kino-teatr.ru/teatr/activist/m/16404/bio/ Никита Долгушин] at the kino-teatr.ru</ref><ref>[https://ria.ru/spravka/20120610/670343057.html Биография Никиты Долгушина] // [[RIA Novosti]]</ref>
In 1959 he graduated from the [[Vaganova Academy of Russian Ballet|Leningrad Choreographic School]] ([[Alexander Ivanovich Pushkin|Alexander Pushkin]]'s course).<ref>[https://musicseasons.org/nikita-dolgushin/ Никита Долгушин. Балетный интеллектуал]</ref>
